how to get mourning dogs to stop dirtying in the house my in laws have three dogs a year old female german shepherd mix a year male old havanese a year old female shi tzu a few days ago the german shepherd mix passed away ever since the other dogs have been peeing and pooping all over their house we realize that they are just upset about losing their buddy and are mourning her loss but this cant go on their house is getting ruined what to do please dont recomend beating them we refuse to do that thanks in advance start potty training over whenever the dog is in the house and not crated put a body harness and leash on the dog tie end of leash to your belt wherever you go the dog goes when you see the dog start to signal sniff circle scratch that it's got to go than run the dog out to where you want it to go praise reward immediately and use a command word consistently when the dog shows it's learned to go outside consistently by dragging you to the outside than you can undo the leash from your belt keep the leash on the dog still and keep an eye on it whenever it is in the house and not crated so if it starts to make an accident you can grab the leash and run it outside once it is going outside with no attempted accidents for at least a week than you can take the leash off the most common mistake in potty training is giving the dog freedom to roam the house without supervision where the human doesn't see the dog signal it needs to go Dog training Housebreaking Crate training German Shepherd Dog Piccolo Junior Saga Aerial (dance move) Tenshinhan Professional wrestling match types Dog agility Dog Operation Market Garden Ferret Futurama (TV series - season 5) Toilet humour Kitesurfing Cerberus Police dog Havanese Pitaten Knots Landing Paranoia Agent Minor characters in Teen Titans (animated series) Eddie Guerrero English cricket team Nintendogs Shaggy dog story Leash Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 Horse Tunisia Campaign StarCraft: Uprising Jennifer Lopez 